            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office.</name>
                    <name type="place">Asylum<lb/>for the Insane</name>
                    <name type="place">London.</name>
                    <name type="place">Ontario</name>
                    <name type="place">London, Ont.,</name>
                    <date when="1889-07-14"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>14 July<handShift
                            rend="printed"/> 188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>9<ptr
                            target="loc.07311_n1"/></date> 
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>If you could only be here, dear Walt, and enjoy this beautiful weather! Today it is
                simply perfect&#8212;the temperature just right&#8212;the sky shaded by a thin veil
                of cloud, a fresh breeze blowing, one cannot but think that the trees, flowers and
                grass must enjoy it all. The old place is lovely&#8212;I wish you could see it!</p>
            <p>All goes quietly and well with us all here and if I could only feel that you were
                having a good time (I am afraid you are not) I should be perfectly happy</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Love to you dear Walt</salute>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
